craterdog.collections.abstractions.AssociativeCollection<K,V>
Type Parameters:
K - The type of the key in the association.
V - The type of the value in the association.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Composite<Sequence<Association<K,V>>>, Sequential<Association<K,V>>, Comparable<Sequence<Association<K,V>>>, Iterable<Association<K,V>>
Direct Known Subclasses:
Dictionary, Map
public abstract class AssociativeCollection<K,V> extends SortableCollection<Association<K,V>>
This collection class implements a sortable collection containing key-value associations. The implementation is optimized for both inserting new associations and looking up values based on their key. The implementation also dynamically scales up and down the number of buckets as the number of associations changes over time.
Author:
Derk Norton
